##Exclusive | 5-day-built "Fireeye" laboratory start-up trial operation, will achieve "suspected full detection" play an important role

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

The "Fireeye" laboratory will provide adequate detection capability for Wuhan and its surrounding cities, and will also serve as an outpost for the "Thor Mountain" , "Fire Mountain" , "shelter" and many other anti-epidemic fortresses, and will provide the solid scientific basis for the front-line staff and the epidemic area crowd to return to work.

By Wong Ki

Wuhan suspected patients have not been diagnosed with the problem, nearly a day or two is expected to be eased. Behind this, just delivered the use of "Fireeye" laboratory in nucleic acid samples detection link, will play a big role.
By Cheng Zhengyu

_
_
_
In the afternoon of February 5th, the COVID-19 laboratory, designed to detect 10,000 people per day, was officially launched for trial operation.

"Fireeye" laboratory by the Wuhan Municipal Government, the Donghu New Technology Development Zone, CCCC second navigation bureau, Shanghai Nori Laboratory, BGI joint construction. Among them, Donghu New Technology Development Zone provided the site, BGI led the design and operation, CCCC second navigation bureau led the construction, Shanghai Nori provided a large number of laboratory equipment. The laboratory occupies an area of about 2000 square meters.
By Cheng Zhengyu

On January 30, BGI completed the design of the lab, and on January 31, the second navigation bureau of CCCC officially started the construction of the lab. After 279 employees of the second navigation bureau of CCCC and Nori in Shanghai volunteered to work overtime and fought tooth and nail, it took only five days, completion of the main laboratory construction.

"Fireeye" laboratory core experimental area total area of 1000 square meters, strictly in accordance with the P2(Biosafety Level 2) laboratory design, equipped with Huada Zhizao high-throughput sequencing overall solutions and equipment, configuration of 30 b 2 Biosafety Cabinet; Batch automated nucleic acid extraction platform with 12 sets of automated extraction equipment, at the same time, equipped with supporting laboratory compartment, sample room, reagent storage, Office area, designed to detect the flux of 10,000 people per day.

The "Fireeye" laboratory will provide adequate detection capability for Wuhan and its surrounding cities, to provide accurate judgment for the diagnosis of fever patients, the screening of high-risk groups, the screening of suspected cases, the isolation of positive infections, and the protection of negative health groups, it will also serve as an outpost for many anti-epidemic fortresses such as "Thunder Mountain" , "Fire Mountain" and "shelter" , and provide a solid scientific basis for front-line employees and people in the affected areas to return to work.

According to the latest data released on the evening of February 6,12,277 cases were detected in Hubei Province on February 5, of which 6,500 were detected in Wuhan. "So far, 35 institutions in Wuhan have been able to run a nucleic acid testing programme that will ensure that all suspected cases added yesterday will be tested today. "
At present, Hubei has 97 testing institutions carrying out nucleic acid testing. The Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention and 83 laboratory inspectors from 17 provinces have reinforced Hubei, which has a daily detection capacity of up to 10,000 under saturation conditions, the release said. On February 5, the province tested 12,277 samples, of which 6,500 were from Wuhan.
However, we can still see the pressure of medical diagnosis and treatment of NCP in Hubei Province from another data: As of 24:00 on February 5,90,997 close contacts had been tracked in Hubei Province, and 64,127 were still under medical observation. Many of these large populations will need to be tested.
By Cheng Zhengyu
Last night (February 6) , Bgi gave an interview to the Xinmin Weekly magazine to describe the operation of the eye of fire laboratory.
_
_
_
Xinmin Weekly: Fireeye, which was launched on February 5, is now receiving samples? When does it go live? When will it be possible to measure, people a day?
_
_
_
BGI: The "Fireeye" laboratory will operate efficiently under the deployment of the new pneumonia control headquarters in Wuhan. After the overnight test run on February 5, the theoretical flux of the "Fireeye" laboratory reached 4,000 person-days in the afternoon of February 6.
We are currently in the process of commissioning the RNA and optimizing the entire testing process. With the completion of the relevant trial run procedures, we will step up the detection flux according to the unified deployment and actual requirements of the Wuhan new pneumonia control and Prevention Headquarters.
_
_
_
Xinmin Weekly: In addition to volume, we're particularly looking for speed. According to the best running condition, how fast can a person's sample test be finished?
_
_
_
BGI: A single sample is manually extracted and PCR tested for RNA in about 3 hours. However, when processing large-scale samples, the overall completion time will be affected by the sample information flow, scheduling of large-scale production and so on.
At present, BGI in the receipt of CDC and hospital samples, guaranteed within 24 hours of the test results.
The "Fireeye" laboratory is equipped with the automatic sample preparation system (MGISP-960) , which can automatically extract samples on a large scale, greatly speeds up the extraction of nucleic acids with speed-limited flux, and improves the detection speed of large-scale samples.
By Cheng Zhengyu

_
_
_
Xinmin Weekly: How hard is everyone working? Are you a little short on manpower?
_
_
_
BGI: The lab needs a team of at least 150 people working in shifts of three to 24 hours a day to keep fireeye running at full capacity for 10,000 people.
_
_
_
Xinmin Weekly: The lab has 12 automated testing machines. Can they significantly help speed up testing?

_
_
_
BGI: In the current COVID-19 testing, the virus nucleic acid of suspected samples is extracted by manual operation, which is the biggest "bottleneck" restricting the speed of sample detection, it also increases the potential risk of viral infection among front-line health care workers.

By loading the automatic sample preparation system, the efficiency of virus nucleic acid extraction of suspected samples can be greatly improved, the speed of detection and identification of new coronavirus can be greatly accelerated, and the problems of slow detection and difficult diagnosis of virus can be solved, it provides a powerful tool guarantee for epidemic prevention and control.
At present, the automatic sample preparation system MGISP-960, which is equipped in the Fireeye Laboratory, has obtained the registration certificate of the Hubei Provincial Drug Administration, and can realize one-stop nucleic acid extraction, with a high degree of automation, and no human intervention after being put on the machine, the automated extraction process takes just an hour to speed up case detection in large-scale population screening.
The device can take 36-96 samples per hour, one person at a time to operate three, greatly improving the efficiency of manpower, to meet the current high-throughput screening emergency needs.
_
_
_
Xinmin Weekly: The fireeye lab was built in just five days. Is it any simpler than a regular lab?
_
_
_
BGI: At a normal speed, a laboratory of this size would take at least 3 months to build with complete materials. We are especially grateful to the construction team for handing over the second navigation bureau and the equipment support team, Shanghai Nori, as well as the tremendous efforts made by other co-construction units for the efficient construction of the "Fireeye" laboratory, they have been working hard with BGI personnel for days, let "Fireeye" laboratory in 5 days in strict accordance with the P2(Biosafety Level 2) laboratory design, and meet the test operation requirements.

_
_
_
"The Xinmin Weekly" : a few days ago, BGI launched the "Ten Thousand People Virus Detection Center" initiative, now "Fireeye" laboratory is what is the resources to respond to the initiative?
_
_
_
BGI: After the launch of the "million-person Virus Detection Center" initiative, the construction of the "Fireeye" laboratory has received 4 donated instruments from Xi'an Tianlong Science and Technology Co. , Ltd. and Tiangen biochemical technology (Beijing) Co. , Ltd. , as well as Henan Province Youth Development Foundation 2 million yuan donation (for clinical testing and related research and development) and IDG capital 1 million yuan donation (for "fire eye" laboratory construction) .
The BGI Hubei team sent the kit to Huanggang

_
_
_
Xinmin Weekly: In recent days, the epidemic in other areas of Hubei is worsening, and their detection gap is very large. What is BGI's next action plan for these areas?
_
_
_
BGI: Bgi Kit has been used in some disease control departments and hospitals and has been reserved, and the disease control and clinical evaluation are positive. As the epidemic situation enters a critical period, we will do our best to serve the needs of epidemic prevention and control. Hope that Wuhan, Hubei and the country's suspected cases can be the first time to use the kit, so that each suspected case can be confirmed as soon as possible.

BGI's pathogen delivery teams in Wuhan, Shenzhen and Tianjin are on standby to ensure timely delivery of test results, providing the fastest feedback for epidemic prevention and control.

By Wong Ki

Wuhan suspected patients have not been diagnosed with the problem, nearly a day or two is expected to be eased. Behind this, just delivered the use of "Fireeye" laboratory in nucleic acid samples detection link, will play a big role.
